				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Textures are flexible, tepples. Lots of formats are supported by most cards. It's the hardware's job to unpack the texture and render it to its backbuffer, whatever format the backbuffer happens to be in.<br /><br />This is also one of the reasons why it's more common to do your software rendering to a texture, and then draw it to the backbuffer with a fullscreen quad. If you make a texture you can specify the format a lot more directly, whereas the backbuffer will only support a limited set of formats, very unflexible.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
